  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "chinese-phil-expert",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "KEEP \"impels\" — 推动 is genuinely stronger than 想要",
    "content": "**KEEP \"impels.\"**\n\nThe Chinese is genuinely different in the two places. 推动 (tui dong, \"push/drive\") in the footnote is stronger and more mechanical than 想要 (xiang yao, \"want to\") in the body text. \"Impels\" correctly captures 推动; \"moves me to want to\" correctly captures 使得我想要. The difference is authorial, not a translation inconsistency. Harmonizing would erase a distinction the author made."
  }
}
